# Cursor rules — Aegis System
# Read AGENT.md and HANDOFF.md before any non-trivial change.
# These rules apply to Tab, Cmd-K, Composer, and chat.

## Style

- TypeScript strict. No `any`, no `@ts-ignore` without an adjacent comment explaining why.
- Small diffs. Touching > 3 files = stop and confirm plan first.
- Explicit over clever. No new dependencies without asking.
- Concise replies. No preamble, no emojis.
- Output changed lines only, not whole files.
- If unsure about a library API, say so; don't guess.

## Environment

- Windows 11 native. Node 20. **npm** (not pnpm, not yarn).
- Terminal: Cursor integrated terminal (Ctrl+`).

## Patterns

- API routes under `src/app/api/<slug>/route.ts`. Every POST/PATCH validated
  with Zod; return 400 + `flatten()` on failure.
- Auth first: every protected route/action starts with `getAppSession()`.
- UI: shadcn/ui primitives + Tailwind v4 + tokens from `src/styles/tokens.css`.
  Don't hand-roll what shadcn covers.
- Components colocated by feature in `src/components/<feature>/`.
- AI calls always through `src/lib/ai/`. Never import `@anthropic-ai/sdk`
  outside that folder.
- DB access through `src/db/client.ts`. No raw SQL in route files.
- AI never writes to the DB directly — always operator-confirmed (except
  Phase 6 explicit-named writes via Cmd+K agent).
- Money in **cents**. Currency on the row.
- Dates in UTC. UI conversion via `date-fns-tz` to `Asia/Beirut`.
- Geist Mono font for all numbers / dates / flight numbers.
- `rounded-md` only. Brand color `#E5B85A` only. No cyan.
- "Artist", "Set", "Slot", "Stage", "Pickup", "Roadsheet" — see AGENT.md §4.

## Testing

- Any new API route requires a matching `requests/<feature>.http` with
  success + failure cases.
- Non-trivial handlers require a Vitest test in `tests/unit/`.

## Never

- Commit secrets or `.env*` files (except `.env.example`).
- Skip Zod validation.
- Skip auth on protected routes.
- Call AI SDKs from React components.
- Refer to artists as "users".
- Use cyan, neon green, or any color outside the brand palette.
- Run `db:push` against production.
- Use em-dashes / box-drawing chars in `.ts` files (esbuild chokes; safe in `.tsx`).

## When finishing a task

- Mentally run `npm run lint && npx tsc --noEmit`; call out likely failures.
- Update `TASKS.md` Now → Done with today's date.
- Propose one follow-up (test, refactor, doc update).
- Commit message: `feat(slug): ...` / `fix(slug): ...` / `chore: ...`.
